Condolences have started to pour in following the news of the passing of Princess Thembi Zulu-Ndlovu, sister of the late Amazulu King Goodwill Zwelithini. Princess Thembi has been wheelchair-bound for the last few years.  It’s believed she died in a hospital on Friday afternoon. Princess Thembi’s last public appearance was at the pre-wedding ceremony of her nephew, King MisuZulu in Newcastle last weekend. This despite her not recognising King Misuzulu as successor to the Amazulu throne. King Zwelithini kaBhekuzulu’s sister, Princess Thembi Zulu-Ndlovu passes away: Ayanda Mhlongo 